  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project objective is to assist Danish companies to avoid that their trade with soja, palm oil, beef and leather affects the world&apos;s forrests and environment negatively. The project will provide companies with knowledge and tools for identification and mitigation of the risks for unacceptable social, environmental and legal practices in their supply chains. Focus is on forest related products, however, the project&apos;s methodology can also be used in risk control in trade of other commodities where the risk for CSR-violations are high. The project wil collect and share information on specific CSR-related risks in selected geographic areas. This will help suppliers in developing countries to meet growng CSR-reporting demands from Danish buyers. Experience shows that Danish buyers can no longer externalise resonsibility and assume that their suppliers will find the solutions on their own.</narrative>
  </description>
